@table @asis

@item Additional Metadata Views
OpenGIS specifications propose several additional metadata views.
For example, a system view named @code{GEOMETRY_COLUMNS} contains a
description of geometry columns, one row for each geometry column
in the database.

@item Functions to add/drop spatial columns
OpenGIS assumes that columns can be added or dropped using special
@code{AddGeometryColumn()} and @code{DropGeometryColumn()}
functions. In MySQL, this is done using the @code{ALTER TABLE},
@code{CREATE INDEX}, and @code{DROP INDEX} statements instead.

@item Factors related to Spatial Reference Systems and their IDs (SRIDs):

@itemize @bullet

@item
Functions like @code{Length()} and @code{Area()} assume a planar
coordinate system.

@item
All objects currently are considered to be in the same planar
coordinate system.

@end itemize

@item The OpenGIS function @code{Length()} on @code{LineString} and @code{MultiLineString} currently should be called in MySQL as @code{GLength()}
The problem is that it conflicts with the existing SQL function
@code{Length()} that calculates the length of string values,
and sometimes it's not possible to distinguish whether the function is
called in a textual or spatial context. We need either to solve this
somehow, or decide on another function name.
@end table


